events.name: Golden State Warriors at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 24 points, Draymond Green fell just short of a triple-double and the weary Golden State Warriors beat the Indiana Pacers 111-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors use late run to pull away from Pacers, 111-107

headlines.description: — Danilo Gallinari set an Atlanta franchise record with 10 3-pointers in a 38-point spree that carried the Hawks to a 127-112 rout of the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gallinari hits Atlanta-record 10 3s, Hawks rout Celtics

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen tied his career high with 26 points, grabbed 18 rebounds and blocked four shots as the Cleveland Cavaliers pulled away for a 112-96 win over Houston on Wednesday night, extending the Rockets’ losing streak to nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers hand Rockets ninth straight loss, 112-96

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler and the Miami Heat are continuing to claw their way back from a brutal start to the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler leads Heat to 4th straight win, 116-108 over Raptors

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine celebrated his first All-Star selection with 35 points against his original NBA team, helping the Chicago Bulls beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 133-126 in overtime Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 35 as Bulls beat Timberwolves 133-126 in OT

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 32 points in his first game since being named a first-time All-Star, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Detroit Pistons 128-118 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson leads Pelicans past Pistons, 128-118

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored a career-high 42 points and Lu Dort hit a 3-pointer as time expired to give the Oklahoma City Thunder a 102-99 win over the San Antonio Spurs on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 42 as Thunder top Spurs 102-99

headlines.description: — Malik Monk scored 29 points, LaMelo Ball added 20 points and eight assists and the Charlotte Hornets cooled off the Phoenix Suns with a 124-121 victory Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Malik Monk scores 29 points, Hornets cool off Suns 124-121

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert and Jordan Clarkson each scored 18 points and the Utah Jazz routed the Los Angeles Lakers 114-89 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert, Clarkson lead Jazz to 114-89 rout of Lakers
